<p>A Slovak court sentenced Juraj Cintula to 21 years in prison for committing a terror attack by shooting Prime Minister Robert Fico, concluding a high-profile case that gripped the country [bbc.com#1][euronews.com#1][straitstimes.com#1][arabnews.com#1]. Prosecutors said Cintula fired five shots at close range in the town of Handlová on May 15, 2024; Fico survived after emergency surgery [bbc.com#1][politico.eu#1][lemonde.fr#1][arabnews.com#1]. The ruling brings legal closure while the political conversation around the attack continues, with Fico previously forgiving the assailant and the government blaming &quot;hatred&quot; spread by opposition and critical media for the climate around the incident [politico.eu#1][aljazeera.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/NiUnM-94tKr9aSS5wg9an_a2Xddy2IXbBvL3KljYmphAmh11kWE7jdU_x1XfmhIcp6wt1sVaYrZQ0yj_PzbNzfr4MEQAHfX3ZtFiZN5-CSw-JziEFd64qm_MicYNCOWORhhWa1CxPw6I_dSnqJoCo3NNzJcJmUqc6Ktqys3_qd0pshu0CnbbI0Le2S5bLt4xD-z9' alt='Juraj Cintula stands in the courtroom in Banská Bystrica for the verdict and sentencing.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Court venue: The verdict was delivered by the Specialized Criminal Court in Banská Bystrica, central Slovakia [firstpost.com#1][lemonde.fr#1].</li><li>Charge upgrade: Authorities initially charged attempted murder, but prosecutors later upgraded the case to terrorism, which the court upheld [politico.eu#1][euronews.com#1].</li><li>Sentence context: Cintula faced up to 25 years but received 21, with the court factoring in his age, according to reporting from the trial [politico.eu#1].</li><li>Stated motive: Cintula reportedly told police he wanted to injure Fico and disagreed with the prime minister’s Ukraine policy, among other issues [politico.eu#1].</li><li>Next steps: The defense says it will appeal the terrorism conviction to Slovakia’s Supreme Court [politico.eu#1][lemonde.fr#1].</li></ul><blockquote>A scream against fear that is paralysing society, - Juraj Cintula</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Prime Minister Robert Fico: Earlier signaled personal forgiveness for the attacker and blamed the opposition for stoking a climate that led to the attack. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/gunman-poet-who-shot-slovakia-pm-robert-fico-jailed-21-years/'>Politico Europe</a>)</li><li>Defense team: Will challenge the terrorism conviction at the Supreme Court. (<a href='https://www.lemonde.fr/en/international/article/2025/10/21/slovak-court-delivers-21-year-jail-term-to-man-who-shot-pm_6746636_4.html'>Le Monde</a>)</li><li>Slovak government: Argues the attack grew from &quot;hatred&quot; spread by opposition parties and critical media. (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/21/slovak-court-sentences-pm-ficos-attacker-to-21-years-for-terror'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li><li>Court/prosecutors: Determined the act met terrorism criteria rather than a lesser offense. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/c051mj72ddjo'>BBC</a>)</li><li>Juraj Cintula: Said he intended to injure Fico and opposed his policies, including on Ukraine. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/gunman-poet-who-shot-slovakia-pm-robert-fico-jailed-21-years/'>Politico Europe</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/gunman-poet-who-shot-slovakia-pm-robert-fico-jailed-21-years/'>Gunman-poet who shot Slovakia’s Fico handed 21 years in prison</a> - politico.eu</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/Slovak-PM-Ficos-attacker-convicted-of-terrorism-jailed-for-21-years'>Slovak PM Fico&#x27;s attacker convicted of terrorism, jailed for 21 years</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/21/slovak-court-sentences-pm-ficos-attacker-to-21-years-for-terror'>Slovak court sentences poet that shot PM to 21 years for ‘terror attack’</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rt.com/news/626757-fico-shooter-sentenced-terrorism/'>Pro-Ukraine activist sentenced to 21 years 